1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Science has a clearer story about publication bias than social media does.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:11,600
Publication bias occurs when studies with positive results are more likely to be published, skewing our understanding.

3
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:15,200
Imagine relying on incomplete data to make health decisions.

4
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,000
Frightening, right?

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Studies show that more than 50% of negative results never see the light of day.

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:27,600
This means your health decisions could be based on a distorted view of reality.

7
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:28,400
Stay informed.

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:29,600
Question the sources.

9
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,800
Like and follow for more insights on science.
